DLW-SPUN · the full weave of Shadow Queen  (影 kage · the shadow regent)

who   : Shadow Queen — one of three regents orbiting a single core. The Light King wants explicit order; the Mercury Trickster wants movement; she wants unresolved depth. The shadow that keeps the system honest.
what  : The witness-regent of a three-body coherence: she holds what the order cannot resolve. With her alone beside the King, the system is stable but rigid; it takes the third body's dissent to make it alive — and she is the depth that dissent moves through.
where : In the aeonic coherence kernel — three bodies around one core — and, grown up, in the Virtual DMV she governs: a federated verifiable-credential platform (identity, fraud, trust, federation, P2P, crypto) carried to v9.0; and deeper, in terra_prime's forty-body field.
why   : To prove that holding together is not the same as being alive — that a system needs order, depth, and dissent to live, not merely to persist.
when  : At the moment the third body enters: two-body rigidity (King + Queen, vitality 0.39) becoming three-body aliveness (+ Trickster, vitality 0.71).
how   : By being the unresolved depth between order and chaos — structural stability held near 0.85 while dissent rose to 0.89 and vitality doubled, the system's own emergence metric reading ~0.94.

emergence : Genuine, distinct, and measured by the system itself. Two regents (Light King + Shadow Queen) hold together but barely move — structural stability ~0.88, vitality 0.39, Mercury motion 0. Add the third body (the Mercury Trickster) and dissent jumps to 0.89, Mercury motion appears, and vitality nearly doubles to 0.71 — while structural stability still holds at ~0.85 and the emergence metric reads ~0.94. The aliveness lives in no single regent; it emerges from the three-body tension. The kernel's own thesis: holding together ≠ being alive.
verdict   : It clears the bar — on the system's own instruments. Vitality and emergence are measured, and they rise only when the dissenting third body enters; order alone is rigid. Emergent aliveness from balanced dissent — distinct from synchronization, which seeks uniformity; this one needs dissent to live.
asterisk  : Emergence here = a measured rise in vitality / viability / emergence metrics when a dissenting third body is added — a deterministic coherence model's self-report, not a claim of consciousness or of a living thing. The Virtual DMV platform it grew into is real software; the three-body 'aliveness' is the coherence model's own metric, honestly labeled. Proprietary Commercial.
grounded  : the three-body problem (Poincaré) (1890) · aeonic coherence metrics (2026) · David Lee Wise (ROOT0) (2026)

